    <note>Ling(1) Zhen [15085] Under Zhao(1) Duanzong [9017], he was commander of the troops that regained Haizhou. He later became Guangdong Zhizhi shi and his descendants lived in Lingnan. This is based on two articles in Lingshi zongxin huikan, 1958, #1, a journal apparently devoted to matters about the Ling lineage. His generational name is the same as Yun [15084], a grandnephew of Kui [15083]. I link him as a younger cousin of Yun although they may be brothers. Yun also held office in Guangdong. CBD, 3, 1728.</note>
